  <element name="Tromplöte" type="Magic Item" source="Magwa’s Magic Item Compendium" id="ID_MMIC_TROMPLOETE">
    <description>
      <p>An infamous bard who could not decide between being a trumpeter or a flutist built this abomination instead.</p>
      <p class="indent">You can use your action to toot the Tromplöte. Roll a d4 to determine the spell that follows (DC14):</p>
      <p class="indent">1: Thunderwave as a 2nd level spell </p>
      <p class="indent">2: Minor Illusion (sound only) </p>
      <p class="indent">3: Vicious Mockery on a random creature </p>
      <p class="indent">4: Shatter (around yourself) </p>
      <p class="indent">After using it twice, you have to finish a short rest to use it again. </p>
      <p class="indent">(Requires tovacco (no one knows why).)</p>
    </description>
